replies.body:
Speaking from someone who plays Lucian, I don't think that Lucian himself is the problem. He hasn't been for a long time. What I always tell people is that Lucian is only broken when a new build is discovered that makes him OP. Think Korean armor pen Lucian and the new BOTRK BC build. Before these builds came along he was fine back in early S6.

Riot wants to keep short range, so there's not really a way to balance him besides tweaking his damage, and we all know how that tends to turn out. {{champion:104}} {{champion:429}}

Honestly, if they gave him a little of his range back, reverted the Q damage changes, and forced him to build crit he wouldn't be nearly as much of a problem. The BOTRK BC build is way too overloaded in stats.
